description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Come and achieve your nursing potential at Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust (NUH), rated ‘outstanding’ for caring by CQC, and the only organisation in Europe with ANCC Pathway to Excellence® and Magnet® recognised Hospitals. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us at our next recruitment event, find out more about our organisation where we are committed to international excellence in nursing care and patient outcomes.&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nottingham University Hospitals (NUH) Band 5 Recruitment Day | Saturday 28th November 2020 | Venue to be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We can offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A dedicated Institute of Care Excellence, offering continuing professional education, careers coaching and development opportunities including: a well-established preceptorship programme, an acute care skills foundation course, bespoke rotational programmes, resilience-focused clinical supervision, an international OSCE programme, Chief Nurse Junior Fellowships and clinical academic careers. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Access to the biggest established Shared Governance programme in the UK, with over 80 staff councils at ward level and growing, giving our workforce a voice and supporting a culture of innovation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An ambitious and forward-thinking professional environment, recognised for empowering nurses to lead and innovate. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Utilising evidence base practice and research to advance nursing science and compassionate care. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supporting collaboration across teams and shared learning. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our nursing teams are Patient Experience Network National Award winners (2018) and finalists in (2019)and have opportunities to work on improvement initiatives that are co-produced with those who use our services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re now recruiting across all of our divisions. Please note this advert is for &lt;strong&gt;Critical Care&lt;/strong&gt; only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in applying for - -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt; - see vacancy 164-2730920&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adult Nursing&lt;/strong&gt; - see vacancy 164-2730892&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking both fully registered and student adult nurses, theatre and recovery practitioners qualifying in the next 12 months. We also welcome international nurses wanting to join our successful OSCE Programme, who have completed language requirements, CBT part one and in receipt of an invitation from the NMC to sit the Test of Competence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lucy Gillespie Lucy.Gillespie@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recruitment Team Recruitment@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
